Assertions are used to ensure that the length of the TaskList increase
in length by 1 after each time the todo, deadline, even commands are
executed.

Assertions are used to define assumptions about the program state so
that the runtime can verify them. An assertion failure indicates a
possible bug in the code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change minor code quality. Remove testing printf statements.
commitResults.messageBody:
Used the KISS to cut down on redundant code in Storage.java.
Cleaned up printf statements to improve the readability of the code.

Duplicated task may cause confusion to users as it is difficult to
differentiate tasks of the same name.

Ensures that users do not add duplicated task with the same name
to the task list. In the event that when a duplicated task is added, a
warning is given instead. Informing the user that there is already a task
with the same name in the task list.

This feature aims to improve user experience by reducing user error.
